               <head>Faṣl al-khiṭāb by Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā</head>
               <msContents class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85089787">
                  <summary>The well-known encyclopaedia of Sufism by Muḥammad ibn Maḥmūd al-
							Ḥāfiẓ al-Bukhārī called Muḥammad Pārsā (d. 822/1420). </summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <author key="person_65292796">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā, 1338
									or 9-1420</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">خواجه محمد پارسا</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8662">Faṣl al-khiṭāb </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">فصل الخطاب</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم و ... الحمد لله الدال
								لخلقته علی وحدانیته باعلامه...</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">... داری گرد دل خویش کرد و صلی الله علی ووو علی
								آله و صحبه و سلم تم الکتاب</explicit>
                     <colophon>... الارباب ملهم الخیر و الصواب و ذلک فی ... یوم... عشرین
								رمضان المبارک فی مسجد الحرام فی سنه ست و سبعین و تسعمائه سنه
								۹۷۶</colophon>
                     <colophon>Colophon dated at the 'Masjid al-Ḥarām', 20 Ramazan 976 AH (8
								March 1569) </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>ff. ii+i+431+i+iii <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>195</height>
                              <width>150</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>150</height>
                              <width>80</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>India Office stamped foliation and Persian foliation on the
										first 100 folios. </p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>Catchwords.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>The first and last folios are considerably damaged.
										Worm-eaten and damp-stained. Rearranged, gauzed and rebound
										by the India Office. </p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="19">
                           <p>19 lines per page.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote medium="ink">
                        <p>Naskh; copied in black ink, with headings, overlinings and marks
									for separating some Arabic phrases in red. </p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Corrections, additions and comments in the margin, mostly in black, additional headings in
								red.</p>
                     <p>Corrections approved with the word <term xml:lang="fa">صح</term>.
                     </p>
                     <p>An undated, partially legible, note on <locus n="1r">f. 1r</locus> describes the
								manuscript as of medium-sized official (<term>vazīrī</term>) paper,
								in naskh script, of 21 lines, written on white paper, and with a
								binding made of marbled paper with red paper doublures.
                     </p>
                     <p>A fragment attached to the unnumbered folio following f. 431,
								contains a partially preserved note praising God and the Prophet
								Muḥammad. </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1910" notAfter="1940">
                        <decoNote>Red half-leather India Office binding dating from the
									early 20th century. </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <seal subtype="oval" type="stamp">
                        <p>Black Government of India Delhi MSS oval stamp (f. 1r).</p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
